# {{project_name}} Configuration

Generated projects now ship three config entry points:

- `config/server.yaml`: baseline sample used by quick starts
- `config/server.dev.yaml`: development-oriented sample
- `config/server.prod.yaml`: production-oriented sample

## Recommended Usage

Use the profile that is closest to your target environment, then keep local changes inside that file instead of editing every example at once.

Examples:

```bash
go run . serve --config config/server.dev.yaml
go run . serve --config config/server.prod.yaml
```

## Profile Intent

- `server.yaml`: repository-friendly default for first run and smoke tests
- `server.dev.yaml`: debug logging, localhost binding, and developer-safe defaults
- `server.prod.yaml`: release mode, `0.0.0.0` binding, quieter logging, and safer public defaults

## Practical Rule

Keep structural keys aligned across profiles so runtime diffs stay easy to review. Add preset-specific sections to every profile you actually use.
